    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepper-and-spinach-shakshuka-with-feta-and-seeds/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>pepper strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepper-and-spinach-shakshuka-with-feta-and-seeds/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[125ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepper-and-spinach-shakshuka-with-feta-and-seeds/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper and onion have softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and <strong>ground cumin</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepper-and-spinach-shakshuka-with-feta-and-seeds/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock </strong>to the pan</p><p>Increase the heat to high and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 6-8 min or until thickened</p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, add your<strong> spinach</strong> and cook until wilted \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepper-and-spinach-shakshuka-with-feta-and-seeds/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the spinach<strong> </strong>has wilted, make 1 well per person in the tomato sauce and crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into it, then cook, covered for 2-3 min or until the egg is done to your liking \u2013 this is your <strong>pepper & spinach shakshuka</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepper-and-spinach-shakshuka-with-feta-and-seeds/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s] </strong>in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through, then slice into triangles</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pepper-and-spinach-shakshuka-with-feta-and-seeds/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pepper & spinach shakshuka </strong>with the<strong> toasted ciabatta triangles</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with your<strong> pine kernel & seed mix </strong>and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Crumble over your <strong>feta</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
